# The Input : 
There are gonna be two ways the user can predict using this model
1. Through explicitly providing his dataset which must have appropriate columns
2. Another way is using the toggle_bar where the user can play with the toggle at once and then predict using the model by his own custom feature values.

# Side-bar
If the second option is clicked we will make sure that a new sidebar is load and user can input his own values
Also we will use our own back button which will lead back to the two options sidebar

# Page 1
If the user clicks the 1 page then we will preprocess internally and display some info about the data beforehand
This will contain info like head , dimensions, column and etc
If the user fails to give us the requested features with the correct dtype then our system throws a error on that page
Also we will then we have two options :
    Either we can use train-test-split and then predict on the test
    Or we can go with directally preprocessing the dataset and predict directally on the whole set 
    (cause the 2 option is what happen in production I guess)

After this model gives a prediction and we merge the predictions with the y if given and show actual vs predicted value
If only X columns are given then we use X directly to predict using some preprocessing and then directly pass through the pipeline 
(I think in production we have only X and we predict directally using some preprocessing and pipeline)

Once we get the values we either can compare the model performance with actual y
 or
We can just give the predictions with previously extracted shap values , classification report , conf_matrix and roc_auc_curve.

So in short our architecture for this depends on two things whether the y column will be present or not

